text: Sääksmäki is a former municipality of Finland. It was merged with Valkeakoski in 1973. Before that, the municipalities next to it were Kalvola, Lempäälä, Pälkäne, Toijala, Tyrväntö (afterwards Hattula), Valkeakoski and Viiala. Its population from 1970 was almost 4,500. ==Famouse people== *Pehr Evind Svinhufvud, Finland's third president, was born in Sääksmäki 1861 ==Other websites== * Sääksmäki-seura ry, website Category:Former municipalities of Finland
